            {
                "Synonym": "Immune pancytopenia"
            }
        ],
        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare chronic hematologic disorder characterized by the simultaneous or sequential association of autoimmune hemolytic anemia (AIHA; a disorder in which auto-antibodies are directed against red blood cells causing anemia of varying degrees of severity) with immune thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP; a coagulation disorder in which auto-antibodies are directed against platelets causing hemorrhagic episodes) and occasionally autoimmune neutropenia in the absence of a known underlying etiology."
        },
